refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
stringgnupg_decrypt resourceidentifier stringtext
Decrypts the given text with the keys, which were set with gnupg_adddecryptkey before.

&reftitle.parameters;




   identifier

    &gnupg.identifier;



   text



     The text being decrypted.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 On success, this function returns the decrypted text.
 On failure, this function returns &false;.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Procedural gnupg_decrypt example


<?php
$res = gnupg_init();
gnupg_adddecryptkey($res,"8660281B6051D071D94B5B230549F9DC851566DC","test");
$plain = gnupg_decrypt($res,$encrypted_text);
echo $plain;
?>




    OO gnupg_decrypt example


<?php
$gpg = new gnupg();
$gpg->adddecryptkey("8660281B6051D071D94B5B230549F9DC851566DC","test");
$plain = $gpg->decrypt($encrypted_text);
echo $plain;
?>
